atment of uncomplicated arterial hypertension in patients with airway dysfunction." Chest 121 (2002):  230-41[23] Cazzola M, Noschese P, D''Amato M, D''Amato G "Comparison of the effects of single oral doses of nebivolol and celiprolol on airways in patients with mild asthma." Chest 118 (2000):  1322-6[24] Macquin-Mavier I, Roudot-Thorval F, Clerici C, George C, Harf A "Comparative effects of bisoprolol and acebutolol in smokers with airway obstruction." Br J Clin Pharmacol 26 (1988):  279-84[25] Ashrafian H, Violaris AG "Beta-blocker therapy of cardiovascular diseases in patients with bronchial asthma or COPD: the pro viewpoint." Prim Care Respir J 14 (2005):  236-41[26] Baselli LM, Oswald MA, Nashelsky JM "Do beta-blockers worsen respiratory status for patients with COPD?" J Fam Pract 54 (2005):  472-3', 1767365210);
